  "prompt": "What should I do if I lost my Chase debit card?",
  "response": "If you've lost your Chase debit card, follow these steps to protect your account and get a replacement card:\n\n1. **Report the Loss**: Immediately report the lost card to Chase. You can do this through the Chase mobile app or website, or by calling their customer service number at 1-800-935-9935.\n\n2. **Monitor Your Account**: Check your account for any unauthorized transactions. If you find any suspicious activity, report it to Chase immediately.\n\n3. **Freeze or Lock Your Card**: If you still have access to the Chase app or online banking, you can temporarily freeze or lock your card. This will prevent unauthorized transactions until you can get a replacement.\n\n4. **Request a Replacement Card**: After reporting the loss, you can request a new debit card. Chase usually sends a replacement card to your registered address within a few business days.\n\n5. **Update Your Payment Information**: Once you receive your new card, update any automated payments or subscriptions with your new card information.\n\n6. **Change Your PIN**: If you believe your card was stolen and not just lost, consider changing your PIN and reviewing your account for any other security risks.\n\n7. **Sign Up for Alerts**: To stay informed about your account activity, you might want to set up transaction alerts through the Chase app or website.\n\nTaking these steps will help protect your finances and ensure a smooth process for obtaining a new card.",
